President Trump visited Iowa to assess the damage caused by a powerful storm that swept through the state. The storm, known as a derecho, brought hurricane-force winds that caused extensive damage to buildings, infrastructure, and crops. The president declared a major disaster in Iowa and pledged federal assistance to help with the recovery efforts. The storm caused significant damage to the state's agriculture industry, with over half of the corn and soybean crops being damaged or destroyed. The president also discussed the impact of the storm on the state's schools and businesses, and expressed his support for the farmers and residents affected by the storm.